Description: Fragment of a seal-impression made of fine brown Nile clay that was hardened after excavation and shows darker discolouration and partly a glossy surface. The rear shows a convex side with impressions of a textile or leather object, probably a bag. Two thin impressions of a string with a width of 0.15 cm. are visible in the break. At the flat upper side the left half of an impression of an oval scarab-like seal is preserved, the sides are bending downwards and show many finger impressions. The seal shows a circumferential line, in the middle a cartouche can be found (MAa't-kA-Ra)| on top of a nbw sign. To the left of it nTr nfr nb tAwy in a column, the part to the right of the cartouche is broken off.
Acquisition notes: Formerly housed by the Birmingham Museum and Art Gallery and the EES London.
